deck: An embittered scientist uses the body of Optimus Prime to unleash a dangerous plague on the Autobots and, ultimately, the universe.
description: Testing a new heat resistant metal alloy, human scientist Jessica Morgan and her partner navigate their space vessel near a star going nova. Suprisingly, a nearby ship contains the body of legendary Autobot leader Optimus Prime, and the two bring it aboard, revealing that Prime did no perish at the climax of "Dark Awakening." Some time later, two Terrorcons steal a supply of the alloy from Morgan's father's laboratory on Earth, and Jessica is injured. Vowing revenge on any and all Transformers, Jessica's father releases space spores discovered during the nova experiment, infecting the two Decepticons with a violent madness. Soon this Hate Plague spreads across Earth, tainting Autobot, Decepticon, and Human alike.
name: The Return of Optimus Prime, Part 1

deck: Overwhelmed by the burdens of leadership, Rodimus Prime doesn't care too much when the Decepticons steal the Matrix of Leadership away from him.
description: Rodimus is worn out by his responsibility as Autobot leader. Shirking his duty, he goes out for a joyride, but unexpectedly runs into Dead End and Wildrider and loses the Matrix, reverting to his Hot Rod form. The two Stunticons bring the Autobot amulet to Galvatron, who is overcome by its power and orders Scourge to destroy it. Will Hot Rod step up to his duty before something terrible happens to the Matrix?
name: The Burden Hardest to Bear

deck: The Autobots discover a race of aliens who have also experienced persecution from the Quintessons.
description: Battling over a Quadrant Lock Disc, Autobot, Decepticon, and Quintesson forces cross a rip in space and become trapped there, landing on the planet Zimojin. An inhabitant named Katsudan removes Preceptor's Autobot sigil and uses it as the head and face for an ancient robot named Ninjika, explaining it resembles the missing face of this broken defender. But what is the Quintessons' connection to the hidden planet, and why do they fear Ninjika?
name: The Face of the Nijika

deck: All Transformers with animal modes are summoned to battle a being called Tornedron, the little brother of Unicron.
description: An ancient scientist named Primacron lets loose his new superpowered destroyer, a flitting, streaking energy being called Tornadron. Primacron's plan: To absorb the energy of all matter in the universe, wipe the universe clean, and being anew from a clean slate. But a mysterious figure calls out to the animal-form Transformers, luring the Dinobots, Predacons, Terrorcons, Sky Lynx, and Trypticon to his lari to stop the menace of Tornadron.
name: Call of the Primitives

deck: Marissa Faireborn and the Technobots are drawn into a Quintesson deal when they meet Dirk Manus.
description: Dirk Mannis, a dashing scoundrel of a space trader, is under attack by Terrorcon leader Hun-Grrr. Marissa Faireborn of Earth Defense Command and the Technobots save Dirk, but soon discover he is in communication with the Quintessons. The five-faced villains want the Recreator, a matter alteration raygun, from Dirk. Will he sell out the Autobots and his own species for profit and adventure?
name: Money Is Everything

deck: Grimlock gains tremendous intelligence and creates the Technobots.
description: Two alien saboteurs, agents of the Decepticons, infiltrate the new Power Core on Cyberton and overload it with volatile anti-electrons. Four Autobots investigate and successfully stop the power surge, but in fixing the problem Grimlock receives and enormous power surge and gains super intelligence. The Autobots track the anti-electrons to Unicron's head, where a showdown with the Decpticons inspires Grimlock to build new reinforcements: The Technobots!
name: Grimlock's New Brain

deck: When several Autobots interfere with his "business", a powerful crime lord has their minds placed into synthoid bodies, with the help of the strangely familiar "Old Snake".
description: After an attempted theft is thwarted by the Autobots, crime boss Victor Death calls in help to deal with the do-gooder robots. "Ol' Snake," a masked man with a familiar voice, agrees to help Drath prcure his abandoned Synthoid technology. With it, the two lure Rodimus, Arcee, Ultra Magnus, and Springer into a trap. transferring the Autobots' minds into that of blank, fabricated human replicants. Can the Autobots rescue their own mechanical bodies before Drath and Ol' Snake use them in a crime wave?
name: Only Human

deck: The Quintessons, as part of a new attempt at regaining Cybertron, unleash the most dangerous creature known.
description: The Quintessons, still plotting to retake Cybertron from the Transformers they created, devise a plan to release an ancient horror on the planet. They feed the Decepticons false coordinates for the Autobots' new Power Core, tricking the Decepticons into unleashing a failed creation of the Quintessons. Freed from its stasis pod, the huge cyborg monster named the Dweller lumbers to the surface, draining the life force of any Autobot or Decepticon that stands in its way.
name: The Dweller in the Depths

deck: The Decepticons conquer Paradron, a world inhabited by pacifistic Autobots.
description: Cyclonus and Scourge retreat from a space battle with the Aerialbots and inadvertently discover the energy-rich planet of Paradron. Seeking a permanent respite from war, the inhabitants of Paradron are all pacifist Autobots who fled Cybertron eons ago to establish an autonomous colony. Sandstorm, an Autobot Triple CHanger and Paradron citizen, must warn his people of the imminent Decepticon invasion before his tranquil world is forever ravaged.
name: Fight or Flee

description: Proper Japanese Title: 上陸、グルメの島! 美食屋トリコ現る! (Jōriku, Gurume no Shima! Bishoku-ya Toriko Arawaru!)
name: Arrival on Gourmet Island! The Gourmet Hunter Toriko Appears!

description: Proper Japanese Title: 再会トリコとルフィ! 海鮮の実を探せ! (Saikai Toriko to Rufi! Kaisen no Mi o Sagase!)
name: Toriko and Luffy Meet Again! Find the Seafood Fruit!

description: Proper Japanese Title: 走れ最強軍団! トリコとリフィと悟空! (Hashire Saikyō Gundan! Toriko to Rufi to Gokū!)
name: Run, Strongest Army! Toriko, Luffy, Goku!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 来るべき祭典 うごめく“ヤバイ奴ら” (Kitaru Beki Saiten Ugomeku "Yabai Yatsura")

Teppei tries to remember the events that left him seriously injured, and Komatsu is honored by an invitation to participate in a world famous cooking festival!
name: The Upcoming Festival! Dangerous Wriggling Critters!

deck: A demon that takes refuge on the internet is after Willow.
name: I, Robot...You, Jane

deck: Buffy, Willow and Xander are forced to take part in a talent show and that's where they meet Sid.
name: The Puppet Show

deck: Buffy and her friends experience there nightmares. Buffy becomes a vampire, Giles goes blind, Xander is being chase by a clown and Willow gets stage fright.
name: Nightmares

deck: Buffy and Cordelia are kidnapped by an invisible girl.
name: Out of Mind, Out of Sight

deck: Giles discovers a prophecy, that Buffy will face The Master and she will die.
name: Prophecy Girl

deck: The Riddler kidnaps the visiting King Boris. Cliffhanger: Batman & Robin are strapped to giant generator shafts that increase in speed so the centrifugal forces will kill them.
name: A Riddle A Day Keeps the Riddler Away

deck: Batman is able to free his hand to get a Bat-blowtorch out of his utility belt and short circuit the generators before it is too late.
name: When the Rat's Away the Mice Will Play

deck: Gwen Cooper is a police officer investigating a recent string of murders in Cardiff. One night, however, she witnesses a covert group do something incredible - resurrect the dead.
name: Everything Changes

deck: Gwen begins her first day as a member of Torchwood, where the team must go after an alien that absorbs sexual energy.
name: Day One

deck: Torchwood chases a man who possesses an alien artifact. When they get their hands on it, they begin to see events that happened decades ago.
name: Ghost Machine

deck: Ianto has been harboring a dark secret he has been trying to keep hidden since he transferred from Torchwood 1. That secret may put his friends in mortal danger.
name: Cyberwoman

deck: The team investigates the strange world of fairies when they take an interest in a young girl.
name: Small Worlds

deck: The Doctor meets his Daughter!
name: The Doctor's Daughter

deck: The Doctor joins in with a murder investigation with Agatha Christie
name: The Unicorn and the Wasp

deck: When Torchwood looks into some brutal murders in a small town, the team gets cut off from one another.
name: Countrycide

deck: If you have more then 1 shadow you should be worried. Also The Doctor meets his future.
name: Silence in the Library

deck: Tosh meets a strange girl named Mary, who she feels a strong connection with. But what are Mary's true intentions?
name: Greeks Bearing Gifts

deck: A string of murders leads Torchwood to believe that their dead colleague, Suzie Costello, is somehow involved. When they temporarily resurrect her with the Resurrection Gauntlet, strangely, she stays alive.
name: They Keep Killing Suzie

deck: A young man is killed in a car accident, but he feels like he has unfinished business on Earth.
name: Random Shoes

deck: A plane from the 1950s comes through the Rift and lands in Cardiff.
name: Out of Time

deck: Owen goes undercover to investigate an underground fighting ring, where kidnapped Weevils are put into a ring to fight humans for sport.
name: Combat

deck: Jack and Tosh are transported to 1941, where they meet a man named Captain Jack Harkness - the man who Jack took his name from.
name: Captain Jack Harkness

deck: Donna is saved and The Doctor has do something.
name: Forest of the Dead

deck: A trip to a diamond water fall what could possibly go wrong?
name: Midnight

deck: What way should you go to work and how much does it matter?
name: Turn Left

deck: The Rift is active, resulting in people from other points in time merging with the present. Members of Torchwood are being tempted to open the Rift by ghosts from their pasts, which would result in a demon being released on the world.
name: End of Days

deck: Jack Harkness returns to Torchwood. No sooner does he return than somebody from Jack's past returns to him. But is he an ally or an enemy?
name: Kiss Kiss, Bang Bang

deck: Torchwood discovers a plot involving alien sleeper agents, who look like humans and have been implanted with false memories.
name: Sleeper

deck: Tommy is a soldier from World War I, who gets awakened from cryo sleep once a year by Torchwood. Now, he gets his one day of freedom, with Toshiko as his date.
name: To the Last Man

deck: The Doctor + Donna Noble + Martha Jones + Captain Jack Harkness + Torchwood + Sarah Jane Smith + Rose Tyler + Daleks = sheer awesomeness.
name: The Stolen Earth

deck: A meat company is suspected of keeping a dark secret - the source of their meat. Gwen tells her fiance, Rhys, about Torchwood.
name: Meat

deck: The End of an era but for who?
name: Journey's End

deck: It's a normal day at Torchwood. But who is Adam, the mysterious member of Torchwood who claims to have always been with them, and why isn't there any information on him in the database?
name: Adam

deck: Torchwood investigates a strange series of deaths. To that end, Jack brings in Martha Jones - who, like Jack, is a former companion of the Doctor.
name: Reset

deck: The team mourns Owen's sudden death. They decide to temporarily resurrect him to say their final goodbyes. Trouble is, now, he won't stay dead. Meanwhile, a hospital is being attacked by what appears to be the Grim Reaper.
name: Dead Man Walking

deck: Owen tries to deal with his new life - or, more accurately, his "death."
name: A Day in the Dead

deck: Jack befriends some talking archeologist dogs and learns of his location: In the future shaped by years of Aku's evil reign. He vows to help the dogs gain their freedom from a life of enslaved jewel mining.
name: The Samurai Called Jack

character_credits.name: Sir Colin Bartholomew Montgomery Rothchild III

first_appearance_characters.name: Sir Colin Bartholomew Montgomery Rothchild III

deck: On the eve of Gwen's wedding day, she is horrified to wake up with a pregnant stomach. Despite this, she intends to go through with the wedding.
name: Something Borrowed

deck: A ghostly circus act is coming out of film footage to haunt Cardiff. What connection does Jack have with this group?
name: From Out of the Rain

deck: Aku learns of Jack's arrival in the future, and of the help he is giving the dogs. He sends a huge army of insect drones to destroy Jack and the dogs alike. Jack has been busy preparing many traps for them however, and when they arrive the battle begins in earnest.
name: The First Fight

deck: Gwen begins to investigate a series of missing persons, and the trail leads her to Jack.
name: Adrift

description: The Team takes on Lobo and discover a shocking secret.
name: Happy New Year!

deck: The Torchwood team is lured into an abandoned building, which is revealed to be a trap. The members of Torchwood remember the days they were each recruited by Torchwood.
name: Fragments

description: Miss Martian, Beast Boy, Superboy, and Adam Strange arrive on the distant planet Rann to stop the alien infiltration of Earth at its source and clear the Justice League's names.
name: Earthlings

deck: Jack's long-lost younger brother, Gray, is out to hurt everything Jack loves, including his team.
name: Exit Wounds

deck: The Autobots, Jack and Miko find themselves trapped inside a cave with Megatron and Starscream.
name: Rock Bottom

description: The Team and the Justice League confront the Kroloteans—and their newfound allies.
name: Alienated

deck: Torchwood begins to investigate when every child on Earth says, simultaneously, "We are coming."
name: Day One

deck: The team is surprised to learn that Starscream wants to become an Autobot.
description:
Tailgate and Cliffjumper only appear in flashbacks.

This episode is dedicated to the memory of Captain H.L. Larry Cullen (Peter Cullen's older brother who helped inspire Optimus Prime's voice), who died in March 2011.
name: Partners

deck: Torchwood's headquarters is destroyed, Jack is seemingly "killed" in the explosion, and Gwen and Ianto are being hunted by the government. What don't they want Torchwood to know?
name: Day Two

description: Superboy and Blue Beetle battle Intergang; several heroes try to help Roy Harper, who has fallen from grace.
name: Salvage

description: Jaime Reyes searches for a friend, while female members of the team return to Bialya.
name: Beneath

description:
Bart Allen travels to the past to escape an apocalyptic future, and crosses paths with members of the Team and fellow speedsters Jay Garrick, Barry Allen and Wally West along with Iris West and Joan Garrick. The Flash family must also deal with Neutron wreaking havoc in Central City. While Bart Allen seems neutralize Neutron, the future still remains apocalyptic.

The secondary plot of the episode features Red Arrow and Cheshire looking for the real Roy Harper. They arrive in a Tibetan monastery, where according to Cheshire's intel Speedy is kept. It's revealed that they have taken their daughter Lian with them. They enter the building and fight themselves past the guards. After defeating them, they open the door that guards were protecting. In a cryogenic pod they find Speedy.
name: Bloodlines

description: Artemis rejoins the team to defend a critical satellite launch, with only Aqualad and his army standing in their way.
name: Depths

description: The real Roy Harper goes on a path of vengeance against those who ruined his life.
name: Satisfaction

description: Black Manta sends his son on a daring mission that will prove his loyalty to the Light.
name: Darkest

description: The team go on a covert mission that will reveal devastating truths.
name: Before the Dawn

description: After the destruction of Mount Justice, the Team goes to the Hall of Justice to pick up their salvaged belongings. However, Despero and L-Ron turn this into a massive cage fight after trapping the heroes inside. Meanwhile, Captain Atom discusses recent events with Tseng Dangun, the head of the United Nations and the Ambassador, who criticizes the fact that the Justice League keeps secrets from the citizens of Earth. During this time, Black Canary investigates the Reach's interest in the Metagene by interviewing the teens who were abducted and experimented on.
name: Cornered
